\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Definition
A hypothesis is a statement about a population parameter, thus 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

.
 Formally, we want to test whether is significantly different from a certain
 value 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{0}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
H_{0}:\theta=\mu_{0}
\]

\end_inset

which is called 
\begin_inset Flex Bold
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
null hypothesis
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Flex Bold
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The alternative hypothesis
\end_layout

\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
H_{1}:\theta\neq\mu_{0}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the value 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{0}$
\end_inset

 does not lie within the calculated condence interval, then we 
\begin_inset Flex Bold
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
reject
\end_layout

\end_inset

 the null hypothesis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the value 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{0}$
\end_inset

 lie within the calculated condence interval, then we 
\begin_inset Flex Bold
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
fail to reject
\end_layout

\end_inset

 the null hypothesis.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
