\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Do recent male and female college graduates earn the same amount on average?
 This question involves comparing the means of two different population
 distributions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In an RCT, we would like to estimate the average causal effects over the
 population
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
ATE=ATT=E\{Y_{i}(1)-Y_{i}(0)\}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We only have random samples and random assignment to treatment, then what
 we can estimate instead
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
difference\:in\:mean=\overline{Y}_{treated}-\overline{Y}_{control}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Under randomization, 
\emph on
difference-in-means
\emph default
 is a good estimate for the ATE.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
