\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The t-statistic for testing the null hypothesis is constructed analogously
 to the t-statistic for testing a hypothesis about a single population mean,
 thus 
\emph on
t-statistic
\emph default
 for comparing two means is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
t=\frac{\overline{Y}_{m}-\overline{Y}_{w}-d_{0}}{SE(\overline{Y}_{m}-\overline{Y}_{w})}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If both 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{m}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{m}$
\end_inset

 are large, then this t-statistic has a standard normal distribution when
 the null hypothesis is true.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
